ial term along the symplectic action-preserving\ndynamics: its fluctuations are the quantum fluctuations of $g_{\\mu\\nu}$. It is\nshown how symplectic quantization maps to the path-integral approach to\ngravity. By doing so we explain how the integration over the conjugated\nmomentum field $\\pi_{\\mu\\nu}$ gives rise to a cosmological constant term in the\npath-integral.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jan 2021 21:32:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Jan 2021 12:16:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 27 May 2021 21:17:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-31"}
