 giants. To explain the sinusoidal RV variations of Pollux, two\nscenarios are proposed. If the RV period is different from the rotation period,\nthe observed periodic RV variations are due to the hosted planet and the\ncontribution of Pollux magnetic activity is not significantly detected. In the\npeculiar case in which the two periods are equal, we cannot discard the\npossibility that the activity of Pollux could explain the total RV variations\nand that the planet hypothesis would appear unnecessary.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Jan 2021 13:33:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-24"}
